    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Talking About Race</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Longtime public school kindergarten teacher Nancy K Webster letter on July 16 issue on race in America praises young children for being able to commnicate and play with one another0</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>I have spent nearly my entire career as a kindergarten teacher in public schools. While some parents won't talk to one another across cultural and racial walls, their children have no problems communicating, playing and enjoying one another. How is race lived in America? In kindergarten, it is lived together.</p>
        <p>Nancy K. Webster  Miami</p>
      </block>
